student_background %>% 
  select(idcntry,idschool,idstud,bsmmat01,bsmmat02,bsmmat03,bsmmat04,bsmmat05)->temp1

school_background %>% 
  select(idcntry,idschool,bcbg15a,bcbg15b,bcbg15c,bcbg15d,bcbg15e,bcbg15f,bcbg15g,bcbg15h,bcbg15i,
         bcbg15j,bcbg15k)->temp2



temp1$score <- apply(temp1[4:8], 1, mean,na.rm=T)
temp2$state<-apply(temp2[3:13],1,mean,na.rm=T)


env=matrix(0,nrow =1,ncol = 1)
final=cbind(temp1[1,],env)
for (i in c(1:2801)) {
  local=temp1[i,]
  local$env=temp2$state[which(temp2$idcntry==local$idcntry & temp2$idschool==local$idschool)]
  final=rbind(final,local)
  }

final %>% aov(env ~ score, data = .) -> fit
summary.aov(fit)
##               Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value Pr(>F)    
## score          1   29.6  29.609   111.2 <2e-16 ***

## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 186 observations deleted due to missingness
#     

#        

final %>% select(env) %>% distinct() %>% arrange(desc(env))->envdistinct

final[2:2802,] %>% select(score,env) %>% filter(env==2 | env== 3)->stat
t.test(score~env,data=stat)

##  Welch Two Sample t-test

## mean in group 2 mean in group 3 
##        425.3534        358.2982

final[2:2802,] %>% select(score,env) %>% filter(env==2 | env== 1)->stat2

## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  score by env
## t = 2.57, df = 219.62, p-value = 0.01083

##   5.404067 40.955091

##        448.5330        425.3534

  group_by(env) %>% 
  summarise(score=mean(score,na.rm = T)) %>% 
  hchart("column",hcaes(x = env,y =score), name = "score")
final[2:2802,] %>% select(score,env) %>% filter(env==1|env==2 | env== 3)->test
p = ggplot(test, aes(env %>% as.character(),score))

  mutate(yearn=btbg01/max(btbg01,na.rm = T),edunorm=btbg04/max(btbg04,na.rm=T),tot=edunorm+yearn)->temp2

final=data.frame(score=0,edu=0)
tmp=data.frame(score=0,edu=0)

links <- sample_n(link, 3876)
for (i in c(1:3876)) {
local=links[i,]
stat=temp1 %>% 
  filter(idcntry==local$idcntry & idschool==local$idschool &idstud==local$idstud) %>% select(score)

  filter(idcntry==local$idcntry & idschool==local$idschool &idteach==local$idteach) %>% select(edunorm)

tmp$score=stat[1,]
tmp$edu=stat2[1,]
final=rbind(final,tmp)

}
